name: Dividing Monomials
educationalAlignment_1_targetDescription: Use variables to represent numbers and write expressions when solving a real-world or mathematical problem; understand that a variable can represent an unknown number\, or\, depending on the purpose at hand\, any number in a specified set.
educationalAlignment_2_targetDescription: Use variables to represent two quantities in a real-world problem that change in relationship to one another; write an equation to express one quantity, thought of as the dependent variable, in terms of the other quantity, thought of as the independent variable. Analyze the relationship between the dependent and independent variables using graphs and tables, and relate these to the equation.
